        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>This is an agreement binding William Patterson and John Ferrell to Edmund Randolph,
                then Governor of Virginia, for unspecified duties at a salary of fifty pounds. The
                agreement includes a provision that Randolph would issue a licence for marriage
                between William Patterson and Margaret Hippard. The place the document was signed is
                not specified and it lacks the signature of a government official attesting to its
                validity. </p>
        </scopecontent>
